ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Time zone of the site collecting the data
Number of hours between UTC  and local device time
Date based on UTC. The date of which data collection started
Time based on UTC. The time of which data collection started
Date based on UTC. The date of which data collection ended
Time based on UTC. The time of which data collection ended
Sampling frequency of sensor in Hz
Data file 1
type of data file 1
Passive sensor types
Notes: eg., gyroscope, accelerometer, geolocation, screen, bluetooth, wifi

ElementDescription: Manufacturer and model of the phone device
Notes: e.g., iPhone 13, Samsung Galaxy S22, Pixel 7

ElementDescription: OS version of the phone device
Name of the phone application used for sensor study.
Name of phone sensing platform
Name of preprocessing pipeline
